Usage: getRailPrototypeMode [-help] [-domain] [-railModel] [-totalPower]
                            [-quiet] [-nonDefault]

-help                             # Prints out the command usage
-domain                           # Format: -domain {{PD1 <value1> net1} {PD2
                                  # <value2> net2}..} (string, default="")
-railModel                        # Seletc rail model: virtual/existing.
                                  # (enums={virtual existing}, default=existing)
-totalPower                       # total power defined by user.
                                  # (float, default=0)
-quiet                            # Displays the current settings in Tcl list format only
-nonDefault                       # Displays the current settings which are not default settings